{
  "uid": "{{ alert_uid }}",
  "title": "High Disk Inodes Usage",
  "folderUID": "{{ folder_uid }}",
  "ruleGroup": "{{ rulegroup }}",
  "condition": "C",
  "data": [
    {
      "refId": "A",
      "relativeTimeRange": {
        "from": 900,
        "to": 0
      },
      "datasourceUid": "{{ datasourceUid }}",
      "model": {
        "refId": "A",
        "query": "SELECT last(\"inodes_used_percent\") FROM \"disk\" WHERE $timeFilter AND \"device\" !~ /^loop/ GROUP BY time(5m), project, zone, host, interface fill(0)",
        "rawQuery": true
      }
    },
    {
      "refId": "B",
      "relativeTimeRange": {
        "from": 0,
        "to": 0
      },
      "datasourceUid": "__expr__",
      "model": {
        "type": "reduce",
        "expression": "A",
        "reducer": "last"
      }
    },
    {
      "refId": "C",
      "relativeTimeRange": {
        "from": 0,
        "to": 0
      },
      "datasourceUid": "__expr__",
      "model": {
        "type": "threshold",
        "expression": "B",
        "conditions": [
          {
            "evaluator": {
              "type": "gt",
              "params": [90]
            },
            "operator": {
              "type": "and"
            },
            "query": {
              "params": ["C"]
            },
            "reducer": {
              "type": "last",
              "params": []
            },
            "type": "query"
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "interval": "1m",
  "for": "5m",
  "noDataState": "OK",
  "execErrState": "Error",
  "labels": {
    "platform": "{{ project }}",
    "zone": "{{ zone }}",
    "severity": "CRITICAL",
        "type": "{{ (rulegroup | string).split('_')[0] }}"
  },
  "annotations": {
    "summary": "Disk inode usage is critically high on one or more servers.",
    "description": "üßê **Why This Happens**\n- Too many small files created on the filesystem.\n- Log or temporary files not cleaned up.\n- Applications generating millions of small objects (cache, images, etc.).\n\nüîç **Impact**\n- Even if disk space is available, no new files can be created.\n- Critical applications may fail with `No space left on device` errors.\n- System services like logging and package installs can break.\n\n‚úÖ **Immediate Actions for Ops**\n1. **Check inode usage by filesystem:**\n   ```\n   df -i\n   ```\n2. **Identify directories consuming most inodes:**\n   ```\n   sudo find / -xdev -type d -exec sh -c 'echo -n {}: ; find {} -type f | wc -l' \\; | sort -nr -k2 | head\n   ```\n3. Remove unnecessary temporary/log files:\n   ```\n   rm -rf /var/tmp/* /tmp/*\n   ```\n4. Archive or delete unused small files.\n5. If inode exhaustion is frequent:\n   - Consider reformatting with a filesystem that supports more inodes.\n   - Review application behavior for excessive small file creation.\n\n‚ö† **Note:** This alert triggers if `inodes_used_percent` stays above 80% for 5 minutes."
  },
  "isPaused": false
}

